      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match the five target flow-speed operating points within ±5% for flow rate and ±3% for rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "All five experimental operating points (2.5 L/min/2500 RPM through 6.0 L/min/3500 RPM) verified against calibrated flow meter and tachometer records. Maximum deviation: 3.1% flow, 1.8% speed. Acceptance criterion met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within a factor of 2 across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH compared against plasma-free hemoglobin measurements at all five operating points. Maximum ratio of predicted to measured NIH is 1.61; all points within factor-of-2 band. Systematic over-prediction consistent with conservative hemolysis power-law model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
