      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation (NIH, RH index) must directly correspond to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate).",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index RH derived directly from NIH predictions and experimental reference. The RH metric is the regulatory submission QoI. No intermediate surrogates used; direct correspondence confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and blood analogue fluid as the COU simulations.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump with 36% glycerol-water blood analogue at hematocrit-equivalent viscosity. Geometry identical to COU simulation geometry. Validation domain encompasses the full COU operating envelope."
